<%- include ("./partials/toasts") %>
<%- include ("./partials/navigation") %>

<div class="section no-pad-bot" id="index-banner">
    <div class="container">
        <br><br>
        <div class="row center">
            <div class="container ">
                <div>
                    <img class="sugarpic" src="/images/sugar.jpg">
                </div>
                <h1 id=result class="header col s12 results">Results</h1>
                <h5 class="center">Hey <%= user.name %>, check the sugar results below</h5>
            </div>
            <div class="container">
                <div class="row" id="resultCards">
                </div>
            </div>
            <br><br>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="features container">
        <div class="section">

            <!--   Features Section   -->
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col s12 m4">
                    <div class="icon-block">
                        <h2 class="center "><i class="fa fa-question coloured"></i></h2>
                        <h5 class="center">How much is ok?</h5>

                        <p class="light">The World Health Organization (WHO) recommends you consume no more than 50
                            grams of sugar per day.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col s12 m4">
                    <div class="icon-block">
                        <h2 class="center "><i class="fa fa-cookie coloured"></i></h2>
                        <h5 class="center">A sweet by any other name.....</h5>
                        <p>The list below contains some of the most common sugars.</p>
                        <ul class="fa-ul">
                            <li><i class="fa-li fa fa-cookie-bite"></i>Brown sugar</li>
                            <li><i class="fa-li fa fa-cookie-bite"></i>Corn sweetener</li>
                            <li><i class="fa-li fa fa-cookie-bite"></i>Corn syrup</li>
                            <li><i class="fa-li fa fa-cookie-bite"></i>Fruit juice concentrates</li>
                            <li><i class="fa-li fa fa-cookie-bite"></i>High-fructose corn syrup</li>
                            <li><i class="fa-li fa fa-cookie-bite"></i>Honey</li>
                            <li><i class="fa-li fa fa-cookie-bite"></i>Invert sugar</li>
                            <li><i class="fa-li fa fa-cookie-bite"></i>Malt sugar</li>
                            <li><i class="fa-li fa fa-cookie-bite"></i>Molasses</li>
                            <li><i class="fa-li fa fa-cookie-bite"></i>Syrup sugar molecules ending in "ose"
                                (dextrose, fructose, glucose, lactose, maltose, sucrose)</li>

                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="col s12 m4">
                    <div class="icon-block">
                        <h2 class="center"><i class="fa fa-stroopwafel coloured"></i></h2>
                        <h5 class="center">Is there a nutritional difference between the types of sugars?</h5>

                        <p class="light">In short, no. They have taste different due to varying processing
                            techniques but are all 100% carbohydrate.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <br><br>
    </div>
</div>

<script src="js/results.js" async defer></script>